---
import SectionHeading from '../SectionHeading.astro';
---

<SectionHeading
  tag="THE PROBLEM"
  title="Three worlds. No bridge."
  subtitle="Enterprise data security, ML platforms, and AI governance operate in silos. AI Shield connects them."
/>

<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mt-12">
  <!-- Card 1: Traditional Data Security -->
  <div class="bg-bg-secondary rounded-xl p-8 border border-white/5">
    <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-danger/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
      <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-danger">
        <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/>
        <line x1="15" y1="9" x2="9" y2="15"/>
        <line x1="9" y1="9" x2="15" y2="15"/>
      </svg>
    </div>
    <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg text-white mb-2">Traditional Data Security</h3>
    <p class="text-text-secondary-dark text-sm leading-relaxed">
      Tools like Varonis and IBM Guardium protect data at rest — but don't understand AI training pipelines or ML-specific sensitivity.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Card 2: ML Platforms -->
  <div class="bg-bg-secondary rounded-xl p-8 border border-white/5">
    <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-accent-secondary/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
      <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-accent-secondary">
        <ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="9" ry="3"/>
        <path d="M21 12c0 1.66-4 3-9 3s-9-1.34-9-3"/>
        <path d="M3 5v14c0 1.66 4 3 9 3s9-1.34 9-3V5"/>
      </svg>
    </div>
    <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg text-white mb-2">ML Platforms</h3>
    <p class="text-text-secondary-dark text-sm leading-relaxed">
      Databricks, Snowflake, and SageMaker assume clean, compliant data. They don't verify what's in the training set.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Card 3: AI Governance -->
  <div class="bg-bg-secondary rounded-xl p-8 border border-white/5">
    <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-accent-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
      <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-accent-primary">
        <rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"/>
        <path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/>
      </svg>
    </div>
    <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg text-white mb-2">AI Governance</h3>
    <p class="text-text-secondary-dark text-sm leading-relaxed">
      Prompt-level tools like Lakera and Lasso protect outputs — but ignore the training data that creates the risk.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Callout bar -->
<div class="mt-10 bg-accent-primary/10 border border-accent-primary/20 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
  <p class="text-text-secondary-dark text-sm md:text-base">
    <span class="text-accent-primary font-semibold">AI Shield</span> sits between your data infrastructure and ML platforms — the compliance layer that's been missing.
  </p>
</div>
